other_tests.findings: A 7 mm segment V liver hypodensity with suggestion of peripheral enhancement may be a hemangioma, but is too small to accurately characterize. The small large bowel are unremarkable. A blind-ending fluid filled tubular structure extending from the cecum with a hyperemic wall measuring 1 cm in maximal diameter, suggestive of retrocecal appendicitis. Scrotal wall thickening is again demonstrated.
